@Node History "How did it end up like this - /X-PoWeR! - Written by KiLLrAvEn/MYSTiC"
                        - - - ≠†≠†≠†HiSTORY ≠†≠†≠†- - -

   2.6.06   07-Oct-94 New       : Incorporated a new search-routine that
                                  makes ConfScan find a file about 200%
                                  faster! With 'N S U' and 'N T' it finds
                                  a file within 1 sec, ALWAYS! That is
                                  dir-file-size INDEPENDENT!

   2.6.03   24-Aug-94 Fixed     : ConfScan no longer crashes if you have dir-
                                  files with size 0 in your conference.
                                  *Reported by Jake at Last Outpost*

            24-Aug-94 Fixed     : If you didn't have RELATIVE_CONFERENCES,
                                  ConfScan could screw things up. Fixed.
                                  *Reported by Zed on Channel-X*

            24-Aug-94 Improved  : A pause between conferences would also
                                  cause a pause between dirs and that is not
                                  what it is supposed to do. Now it works
                                  without problems.
                                  *Reported by Zed on Channel-X*

            24-Aug-94 Fixed     : If you had the 'Clear Screen' option on,
                                  the screen would also be cleared at the
                                  end of the list, showing only the final
                                  stats, not cool. So I fixed that.
                                  *Reported by Muad'Dib*

            24-Aug-94 Improved  : The Config menu has got a new and better
                                  interface and now has two sections:
                                  environmental options and CS options. Also,
                                  when the config menu is called from 'N' or
                                  'F', the environmental options will show
                                  up first (instead of the CS options that
                                  used to come up first).

            24-Aug-94 Improved  : Wrote a few new help files that are shorter
                                  and (hopefully) easier to read and better
                                  to understand.

            25-Aug-94 Fixed     : If you have the ClearScreen option set, it
                                  will now also clear the screen the first
                                  time.
                                  *Reported by Arcade/MST*

   2.6.02   11-Aug-94 Fixed     : Tagging and flagging of files was a mess!
                                  Things got messed up, nothing went right.
                                  This will fix it, make sure to REMOVE any
                                  file in your ...ConfScan/Users directory.
                                  *Reported by Me*

   2.6.01   07-Aug-94 New       : ConfScan now saves all the files that a
                                  user flags in the sub-directory users in
                                  the ConfScan directory. They are stored
                                  like User_x, where x is the slotnumber
                                  of the user. This has the advantage that
                                  users can logoff, call back and still
                                  have those files flagged.
                                  
                                  If the directory ../Users does not exist,
                                  ConfScan will create it for you.
                                  
                                  For now, this is not an option, I intend
                                  to make at optionable for either the sysop
                                  and user.
                                  *Requested by several sysops*

            07-Aug-94 New       : The flagged files are no longer saved in
                                  text format, a structure is now used for
                                  storage. This decreases readability (if
                                  you ever read them 8-) ), but increases
                                  speed.

            07-Aug-94 Fixed     : ConfScan now also works under /X 4.x.

   2.6.00   24-Jul-94 New       : When a dirfile is being copied (ie. you
                                  have the copy-dirfiles turned on), the
                                  user will see a percentage displaying the
                                  progress of the copy (just like the scanning
                                  routine).
                                  This only happens when you have the USE-
                                  PERCENTAGE option turned on.

                      Improved  : Built in some more error information on 
                                  some parts of the program. Home usage only.

   2.5.63   23-Jul-94 Fixed     : The ConfxCMD bug is gone. I just had to take
                                  a closer look. Ami-Express gives the number
                                  of the current conference MINUS 1. I knew
                                  that, but forgot it later on in the routine.
                                  *Reported by Zed at Channel-X*

                      New       : From now on, registered versions are 
                                  available from me. Registered version do not
                                  have special functions or hidden features,
                                  they are just registered (shown at startup).
                                  The only advantage is that you will most
                                  likely get the current available version.

                      Fixed     : MAJOR BUGFIX! For some incredibly STUPID
                                  reason I forgot to check for hold access
                                  with the 'F' command 8-( My sincere apologies
                                  for such a mistake, how could this slip
                                  through all tests...
                                  *Reported by TyCooN*
                                  
   2.5.62   16-Jul-94 Fixed     : It appears it still does not work properly.
                                  Made a quick fix on-line 8-(
                                  *Reported by Zed at Channel-X*

   2.5.61   11-Jul-94 Fixed     : When installed as an ConfxCMD command, it
                                  would look in the wrong Conference for the
                                  icon information. Is fixed.
                                  *Reported by Zed at Channel-X*

                                  * R E L E A S E  V E R S i O N *

   2.5.60   28-Jun-94 New       : 'N S G' now works. It stands for "New Since
                                  last logon Global" and does the same as
                                  'CS'.
                                  *Requested by EMPiRE/MST*

            30-Jun-94 Changed   : Removed the Beta testers registration info.
            
   2.5.59   26-Jun-94 Fixed     : Changed the header of ConfScan, 'cause
                                  ArCaDe is now also a MYSTiC member.

   2.5.58   20-Jun-94 New       : CTRL-C is now recognized at the flag/tag
                                  prompt in ConfScan.
                                  *Requested by Sal-One*

                      Improved  : Made the tagging routine a little bit more
                                  robust.

   2.5.57   20-Jun-94 Fixed     : Any comments between P/N and the file date
                                  are now shown with a blue background colour
                                  from the P/N to the file date (no more spaces
                                  between the comment and the file date).

   2.5.56   18-Jun-94 Fixed     : The 'P' bug is fixed.
                                  *Reported by Tycoon/MYSTiC*

                      Improved  : Replaced an Execute() routine with System().

   2.5.55   15-Jun-94 Fixed     : I forgot to put a return ('\n') after the
                                  comment line in the callerslog.
                                  *Reported (first) by Muad'Dib/5D*

                      Fixed     : Replaced some of the ESC[M and ESC[K
                                  commands with 79 spaces. I find this
                                  *STUPiD* but there are still terminals
                                  around (especialy on the MS-DOS platform
                                  that DO NOT recognize them!! So incredibly
                                  lame!

                      Changed   : The task priority of ConfScan is now always
                                  0. I used to adjust the priority to the
                                  same as ACP, but that could slow the system
                                  down if you had it above 0. This evens the
                                  CPU time a bit if you have multiple nodes.

                      Fixed     : The temporary files in T: were not removed
                                  if you had 'CopyDirFiles' activated.

   2.5.54   13-Jun-94 Fixed     : The `FileHelp' files for every conference
                                  sometimes were not shown. Fixed it.
                                  *Reported by EMPiRE/MYSTiC*

                      Improved  : The user can now also enter values like
                                  -5 or `T' when ConfScan asks for a date
                                  via a prompt.

                      Fixed     : The 'N' command wouldn't show the existence
                                  of the [H]old dir to people who had access
                                  for it if ConfScan asked for it via the
                                  prompt (Which directory...).

                      Improved  : The output to the Callerslog is now modified
                                  to "Directory Scan from (xx-xx-xx)" to gain
                                  compatibility with some callerslog-scan-
                                  programs.
                                  *Requested by Sal-One/TRSi^ZENiTH*

                      Fixed     : if you had used the 'P' space and filesize
                                  in the filedir (DiRx) for a comment (for
                                  instance "DELETED!"), than the second 'E'
                                  would not be shown. is fixed now.

                      Fixed     : Text-files were not shown with the [V]iew
                                  function (still a result of the multi-
                                  langual stuff... sh*t).
                                  *Reported by TyCooN/MYSTiC*

                      Fixed     : The [V]iew option was not multi-node yet,
                                  fixed that ofcourse.

   2.5.53   06-Jun-94 Fixed     : Due to the new multi-langual stuff in 
                                  ConfScan, the [V]iew function failed in
                                  locating the output of the [V]iew function.
                                  *Reported by Just Another Freak*

   2.5.52   05-Jun-94 Fixed     : The search routine failed sometimes if you
                                  had banners in your dirfiles. This has now
                                  been fixed.
                                  *Reported by Tycoon/MYSTiC*

   2.5.51   04-Jun-94 New       : At the prompt there now is a percentage
                                  shown. it indicates how much of the files
                                  have been shown already.
                                  
                      Improved  : Added credits for Pascal (Arcade).

   2.5.50   02-Jun-94 Improved  : Searching routine has been sped up a
                                  little bit. instead of the stack, i
                                  now use some of the CPU's registers.
                                  Especially 030+ users will benefit
                                  from this. if you don't have an 030,
                                  go buy one! :-)

            03-Jun-94 Improved  : All ConfScan help files can now be made
                                  multi-langual just like in Ami-Express
                                  itself (with .TXT and .TXT.GR). it now
                                  takes the ScreenTypes.info in account
                                  when showing a textfile, meaning that
                                  the helpfile filename is now built up
                                  like this:
                                  
                                  ConfScan.<CMD>.Help<ACS>.<GROUP>
                                  
                                  Where CMD = Command name (f.i. CS)
                                        ACS = Accesslevel, but if the
                                              level is not found, the
                                              <ACS> will be skipped.
                                      GROUP = Language. Factory settings
                                              are .TXT (Mono) and .TXT.GR
                                              (Colour). But you can add
                                              more types in the icon.
                                  *Requested by AtomiX (Here you go ;) )*

            03-Jun-94 Fixed     : The infamous 'f' bug has been removed.
                                  it only occured when you had the "Copy
                                  DirFiles" option on (Sysop Prefs)...
                                  *Reported by Brutus*

            03-Jun-94 Fixed     : Starting a download from ConfScan no longer
                                  causes Ami-Express to perform a fake log-
                                  out if you said 'Goodbye after', this time
                                  the user will be kicked off the board.
                                  THiS WiLL ONLY WORK WiTH VERSiON 3.38+ !!
                                  *Reported by ->>Constrictor<<-*


            03-Jun-94 Improved  : CONFSCAN NOW HAS GOT A FUCKiNG FAST ASM
                                  SEARCH ROUTiNE AND KiCKS ASS! USUALLY
                                  ALL DATES ARE FOUND WiTHiN 2-3 SECONDS!!
                                  
                                  *> ASM CODE WRiTTEN BY PASCAL EEFTiNCK <*
                                  *> THANKS A LOT MAN! iT WORKS GREAT !! <*

            04-Jun-94 New       : At the CS-Prompt (More) you can now enter
                                  a 'P' to manually override the Full Desc
                                  mode giving you a full page of new files
                                  instead of checking for broken file de-
                                  scriptions. This works only for that time,
                                  the next prompt will still use Full Desc
                                  mode (unless you press 'P' again).

   2.5.49   27-May-94 Improved  : What do you know? it's my birthday! :)
                                  Never mind that, I did manage to fit in
                                  something new anyway... if you now press
                                  'Q' in the config menu ('N W') nothing
                                  will be saved.
                                  *Requested by Muad'Dib/5D*
                                  (Thanks for the tapez man :) ).

            27-May-94 New/Fixed : You can now [V]iew files from the hold
                                  dir (but ofcourse only if you have got
                                  hold access).
                                  *Reported by Muad'Dib/5D*

            01-Jun-94 Fixed     : And once again I had to fix the date 
                                  routine 'cause June wasn't recognized
                                  correctly (stupid bug!!!). Sorry guyz.
                                  *Reported by Muad'Dib/5D*

   2.5.48   21-May-94 New       : The /-\ routine has been replaced by an
                                  percentage routine. So instead of the /-\
                                  pointer you get to see a percentage showing
                                  how much of the dirfile has been scanned.
                                  The config program has been changed as well
                                  for this, I just renamed the "Busypointer"
                                  field to "Use Percentage" so if you had the
                                  Busypointer on, you will get the % now.
                                  ** YOU SAW iT HERE FiRST! **

            22-May-94 Fixed     : The 'F' function wouldn't recognize the
                                  hold dir if you didn't specify it at the
                                  prompt. Now it does.

   2.5.47   20-May-94 Improved  : Replaced some old routines with newer and
                                  better ones. This is the finishing up part
                                  before the release.

   2.5.46   17-May-94 Fixed     : The 'F' command wouldn't show the FileHelp
                                  file if you enter it without arguments.
                                  *Reported by Tycoon/MYSTiC*

                      Fixed     : if you had the 'always show full desc' mode
                                  on and you [V]iewed a file, ConfScan was 
                                  confused and tags went wrong. is now fixed.
                                  
                      Improved  : if you have the 'Clear Screen' flag on, the
                                  screen will also be cleared at the start of
                                  ConfScan, not after the first prompt.

                      Fixed     : if you left the 'F' command with enter you
                                  would still get a line telling you that there
                                  were 0 bytes and 0 files.

   2.5.45   12-May-94 Fixed     : Bug in the 'prompt' routine sometimes caused
                                  for an infinite loop, the only way out was
                                  the 'Q' option. is now fixed.
                                  *Reported by Brutus/Brutal Approach*

                      Fixed     : Replaced some old stick-m-together routines
                                  with the AddPart routine. This solves the
                                  problem that ConfScan can't find certain
                                  files (such as dirfiles).
                                  *Reported by Brutus/Brutal Approach*

   2.5.44   10-May-94 Fixed     : Minor bug in the config menu is fixed.

   2.5.43   10-May-94 Improved  : Radical change in the config menu! it now
                                  consists of two menus instead of 1. You
                                  can swap menus with 'Y'. Save/exit with 'Z'.

                      New       : You can have ConfScan always show you the
                                  full description of a file. That means that
                                  if you get the `More' prompt in the middle
                                  of a file description, ConfScan will notice
                                  this and show the next files until that 
                                  file is about to disappear from your screen
                                  showing its full description. This is quite
                                  a nice feature if you ask me ;-) Very nice
                                  and USER CONFiGURABLE.

                      New       : You can have ConfScan clear the screen
                                  after every `More' prompt. This is also
                                  USER CONFiGURABLE. ConfScan will *NOT*
